Introduction

Baekho is a South Korean singer-songwriter and producer who was formerly a member of NU'EST under Pledis Entertainment. He debuted with NU'EST on March 15, 2012, with the single Face and later gained recognition through Produce 101 Season 2 in 2017, where he finished in 13th place. While fellow member Minhyun joined Wanna One, Baekho and the remaining members formed NU'EST W, releasing three mini albums. In 2021, he made his musical debut as Haram in Midnight Sun. Following NU'EST’s disbandment in 2022, Baekho renewed his contract with Pledis and launched his solo career with the mini album Absolute Zero. Since then, he has released multiple digital singles, including Elevator, What Are We, and the collaboration Love Or Die with BIGONE.

In March 2025, Baekho announced his departure from Pledis Entertainment after 13 years, with his final digital single under the agency, Off-Road, set for release on March 14, his last day with the company. His career has been marked by versatility, from idol group promotions to solo music production and theater. As he embarks on a new chapter, fans eagerly anticipate his next steps in the industry.
